2. If you want to customize the configuration of `@DataJpaTest`, please read [this official blog entry](https://spring.io/blog/2016/08/30/custom-test-slice-with-spring-boot-1-4) from Spring.io for this topic,(a little tedious).
3. Split the configurations in `Application` into smaller configurations by features, such as `WebConfig`, `DataJpaConfig` etc. A **full featured configuration**(mixed web, data, security etc) also caused your **test slice** based tests to be failed. Check the [test samples](https://github.com/hantsy/angularjs-springmvc-sample-boot/tree/master/src/test/java/com/hantsylabs/restexample/springmvc/test/slice) in  [my sample](https://github.com/hantsy/angularjs-springmvc-sample-boot).

